01:13:36,829 --> 01:13:40,493
Go against your father's will
because you love your cousin.

941
01:14:06,525 --> 01:14:10,314
For those of you who
want to learn how to cook,

942
01:14:10,446 --> 01:14:15,111
and I always felt <i>The Godfather</i>
at least should give a recipe

943
01:14:15,201 --> 01:14:20,696
every once in a while, this is a pretty
authentic method of rolling gnocchi.

944
01:14:20,790 --> 01:14:25,125
The whole secret of
rolling gnocchi really is

945
01:14:25,211 --> 01:14:27,629
the touch when you flip
them over with your finger.

946
01:14:27,713 --> 01:14:30,045
You can do it with a fork, too.

947
01:14:30,132 --> 01:14:34,968
Gnocchi is made with an equal
part of flour and mashed potatoes,

948
01:14:35,054 --> 01:14:38,843
a little bit of salt, and
you create the dough,

949
01:14:38,933 --> 01:14:42,346
it's really a potato dumpling,
and then you roll it out

950
01:14:42,436 --> 01:14:46,976
in these long tubular
strips as you'll see them do.

951
01:14:47,066 --> 01:14:50,316
Then with a knife cut them into
little three-quarter-inch sections

952
01:14:50,403 --> 01:14:53,987
and then you have to have the touch.
So you need your cousin

953
01:14:54,073 --> 01:14:57,441
to help guide your
finger as you flip it around.

954
01:14:57,535 --> 01:14:59,286
You get a little dimple in the gnocchi

955
01:14:59,370 --> 01:15:01,486
and that's what makes them more tender

956
01:15:01,580 --> 01:15:03,665
so they're not just
like little pellets of lead

957
01:15:03,749 --> 01:15:05,083
when they come out of the water.

958
01:15:05,167 --> 01:15:07,085
When they're cooked
they'll rise to the top,

959
01:15:07,169 --> 01:15:13,290
so you don't have to dump the water.
You can just scoop them off the top.

960
01:15:13,634 --> 01:15:17,878
And, you know, most gnocchi in
restaurants are too soft and mushy.

961
01:15:17,972 --> 01:15:22,557
My gnocchi, I don't know
why, are just a little more firm,

962
01:15:22,643 --> 01:15:24,475
but this is how you roll them.

963
01:15:24,562 --> 01:15:26,599
You see the little dimple?

964
01:15:27,189 --> 01:15:31,808
That's the secret, that little
dimple when they flip over.

965
01:15:31,902 --> 01:15:36,521
I find this love story so sweet,
you know, so touching to me.

966
01:15:36,615 --> 01:15:40,028
And both of them so young and…

967
01:15:40,828 --> 01:15:43,570
I mean this holding of her hand

968
01:15:43,664 --> 01:15:46,952
is just going to make such
unhappiness for the two of them,

969
01:15:47,043 --> 01:15:48,784
it makes me want to cry.

970
01:16:04,351 --> 01:16:07,560
Nothing but trouble will come from this.

971
01:16:07,646 --> 01:16:09,387
And tragedy.

972
01:16:35,549 --> 01:16:37,506
Here we are on very familiar turf.

973
01:16:37,593 --> 01:16:42,087
We're at the Festa of San Gennaro.

974
01:16:42,181 --> 01:16:45,719
The policemen on horseback
is an important element

975
01:16:45,851 --> 01:16:49,765
that's established earlier
and of course, you know,

976
01:16:49,855 --> 01:16:55,100
Joey Zasa, like any number
of civic-minded men of affairs,

977
01:16:55,194 --> 01:16:57,276
John Gotti or others,

978
01:16:57,363 --> 01:17:02,449
you know, really always tried
to reward the neighborhoods

979
01:17:02,535 --> 01:17:04,776
and throw festivals with fireworks

980
01:17:04,870 --> 01:17:08,204
and I think that's what
Joey Zasa is doing here.

981
01:17:08,290 --> 01:17:13,831
The society of Anthony Meucci
is going to raffle off a Cadillac.

982
01:17:13,921 --> 01:17:17,755
Meucci, for those who don't
know, is the Italian-American

983
01:17:17,883 --> 01:17:22,047
who invented the telephone, they
say before Alexander Graham Bell.

984
01:17:22,138 --> 01:17:25,472
At any rate, the two of them
long have been associated

985
01:17:25,558 --> 01:17:27,640
with the invention of the telephone

986
01:17:27,726 --> 01:17:31,560
and Italians always like to
say that it was really Meucci.

987
01:17:31,647 --> 01:17:35,311
But many great technological
inventions have more than one inventor.

988
01:17:35,401 --> 01:17:38,769
Television has three
or four that I can think of.

989
01:17:38,863 --> 01:17:42,151
These great innovations
come about of the times

990
01:17:42,241 --> 01:17:46,656
and sometimes more than one
person thinks of them, so, yes, it's true.

991
01:17:46,745 --> 01:17:49,487
Meucci was an inventor of the telephone.

992
01:17:56,463 --> 01:18:00,502
This is Elizabeth Street in New
York, incidentally where I live

993
01:18:00,593 --> 01:18:03,051
when I'm in New York myself now.

994
01:18:03,179 --> 01:18:06,229
I have a little apartment at
the end of it, maybe I'll see it.

995
01:18:28,704 --> 01:18:33,449
You can see the way the horse
is being woven through this,

996
01:18:33,542 --> 01:18:36,660
somewhat hopefully, mysteriously.

997
01:18:57,858 --> 01:19:02,022
The little girl whose
face is shocked with…

998
01:19:02,112 --> 01:19:04,900
Her name, I think, was
Jessica, a very sweet little girl

999
01:19:04,990 --> 01:19:06,697
and I still get letters from her.

1000
01:19:06,784 --> 01:19:08,240
She must be a big girl now.

1001
01:19:30,224 --> 01:19:34,889
We always wanted to have a coup de grâce

1002
01:19:34,979 --> 01:19:39,268
performed by a guy on a horse,
dressed up as a New York cop,

1003
01:19:39,358 --> 01:19:41,770
so we got to do it for this movie.

1004
01:19:54,999 --> 01:19:59,459
So it was just like <i>Godfather I,</i>
while Michael was clinging for life,

1005
01:19:59,545 --> 01:20:03,129
or in a weakened state,
the family went ahead

1006
01:20:03,215 --> 01:20:07,254
and engaged in violence
which Don Vito Corleone

1007
01:20:07,344 --> 01:20:11,008
would have objected to
and now Michael does.

1008
01:20:11,098 --> 01:20:14,682
Of course, his sister, Connie,

1009
01:20:14,768 --> 01:20:17,635
and his Caporegimes
and Vincent himself said,

1010
01:20:17,730 --> 01:20:21,018
"What were we to do?
They were coming after us."

1011
01:20:21,108 --> 01:20:25,147
And Michael seems to
understand that it has to end.

1012
01:20:25,237 --> 01:20:29,777
That you just can't keep
outsmarting your enemy in this

1013
01:20:29,867 --> 01:20:35,579
back and forth, <i>Oresteia</i> type
of violence begetting violence.

1014
01:20:36,665 --> 01:20:38,827
To do that is to sacrifice your youth,

1015
01:20:38,917 --> 01:20:42,501
because ultimately it
will destroy the future.

1016
01:20:42,588 --> 01:20:45,831
Well, in all the trouble spots
of the world, I always wonder

1017
01:20:45,966 --> 01:20:50,506
in the Middle East and other places,
don't they think of their young people?

1018
01:20:50,637 --> 01:20:55,803
Don't they think that to constantly
trade violence for violence,

1019
01:20:55,893 --> 01:20:57,258
only begets more violence,

1020
01:20:57,394 --> 01:21:00,188
that they're just eating up
their own children, in a way.

1021
01:21:00,272 --> 01:21:05,563
But it goes on, even as I'm speaking
and will, no doubt, long after I'm gone.

1022
01:21:19,917 --> 01:21:21,918
That's a nice set.
That's Dean Tavoularis,

1023
01:21:22,002 --> 01:21:25,415
once again working with us in Rome,

1024
01:21:25,506 --> 01:21:29,044
shooting a film that was
supposedly set in New York in Rome.

1025
01:21:29,134 --> 01:21:32,718
It would have been wise, had
we perhaps had a little budget

1026
01:21:32,805 --> 01:21:36,264
to shoot more of a second
unit in New York than we did.

1027
01:21:36,350 --> 01:21:39,513
We did go around and
shoot streets and entrances,

1028
01:21:39,603 --> 01:21:42,897
but it would've been nice to have
more of the texture of New York in this.

1029
01:21:42,981 --> 01:21:46,849
You don't really feel it as
much as you should, I think.

1030
01:22:04,169 --> 01:22:07,753
Of course one of the
exciting things of this movie

