1054
01:24:06,875 --> 01:24:08,912
And I laughed and smiled

1055
01:24:09,002 --> 01:24:11,835
because I just got such
a kick out of what he did.

1056
01:24:11,922 --> 01:24:15,665
I suppose one could say
that he laid it on a little thick,

1057
01:24:15,759 --> 01:24:19,878
but I certainly enjoyed
it and if it's a little broad…

1058
01:24:19,972 --> 01:24:22,714
It's I who enjoyed it. So I did it.

1059
01:24:22,808 --> 01:24:25,721
I always liked Eli Wallach.
I loved him in <i>Baby Doll</i>

1060
01:24:25,811 --> 01:24:29,270
and he was a pleasure to be around.

1061
01:24:29,356 --> 01:24:34,226
I love the idea of a character
who's this old, old, old, old man

1062
01:24:34,319 --> 01:24:36,686
who's always giving you advice, you know,

1063
01:24:36,780 --> 01:24:39,067
like "Well, I don't have
much longer to live,"

1064
01:24:39,157 --> 01:24:41,239
but really he's going to outlive you all

1065
01:24:41,326 --> 01:24:45,160
and he's going to have
the last laugh, almost.

1066
01:24:45,247 --> 01:24:48,911
His resolution in this movie
is particularly amusing to me.

1067
01:25:05,267 --> 01:25:08,555
And here in another <i>Godfather</i> tradition

1068
01:25:08,645 --> 01:25:14,607
suddenly we're in the beautiful
sunny setting of Sicily and…

1069
01:25:15,819 --> 01:25:18,777
This was a very
beautiful part of the shoot,

1070
01:25:18,864 --> 01:25:21,947
because we were really in Palermo

1071
01:25:22,034 --> 01:25:25,402
and outside of Palermo where
the people are so wonderful.

1072
01:25:25,495 --> 01:25:29,363
And anyone who sees this movie

1073
01:25:30,876 --> 01:25:34,210
and sees Sicily as a beautiful place,

1074
01:25:34,296 --> 01:25:36,628
this is not even a tenth of it.

1075
01:25:36,715 --> 01:25:41,755
It is the most beautiful island and
such sweet and hospitable people.

1076
01:25:41,845 --> 01:25:45,213
I think perhaps that's where
the Sicilians get the reputation

1077
01:25:45,307 --> 01:25:50,473
as being especially tough, it's
only because they are so open,

1078
01:25:50,562 --> 01:25:55,648
and so arms-embraced, that
if you take advantage of them,

1079
01:25:55,734 --> 01:25:58,522
you do something that can only be

1080
01:25:58,612 --> 01:26:02,355
responded to with the
most harsh response,

1081
01:26:02,449 --> 01:26:07,319
because they are very
trusting and great people.

1082
01:26:13,794 --> 01:26:19,506
These were beautiful settings in
Sicily, these wonderful palaces and…

1083
01:26:20,676 --> 01:26:24,715
Indeed, many of them were
the same locations we used

1084
01:26:24,805 --> 01:26:28,639
for the first and second
<i>Godfather</i> pictures.

1085
01:26:28,725 --> 01:26:34,186
This particular villa where he meets with

1086
01:26:34,272 --> 01:26:37,765
the old timers is the very first villa

1087
01:26:37,859 --> 01:26:41,397
where Michael had taken
his young wife, Apollonia.

1088
01:27:04,302 --> 01:27:07,044
Here we have, again,
actors from the past.

1089
01:27:07,139 --> 01:27:10,131
Franco Citti, who was
one of the two shepherds

1090
01:27:10,225 --> 01:27:13,388
who had been Michael's loyal bodyguard,

1091
01:27:13,478 --> 01:27:16,971
is now back, more elderly.

1092
01:27:17,065 --> 01:27:22,060
This is a new actor, playing the
part that Corrado Gaipa played,

1093
01:27:22,154 --> 01:27:27,274
if you remember, the old uncle
who had taken care of Michael

1094
01:27:27,367 --> 01:27:30,280
when he stayed at the villa.
This is his villa.

1095
01:27:32,497 --> 01:27:36,331
The name Lucchesi is
the man I referred to earlier,

1096
01:27:36,418 --> 01:27:41,504
who was the gentleman with the
thick black glasses and represents,

1097
01:27:41,590 --> 01:27:46,585
I won't say his name, the highest level
of political power at that time in Italy

1098
01:27:46,720 --> 01:27:51,806
and only recently has been
through many, many inquiries,

1099
01:27:51,892 --> 01:27:54,350
regarding his association with the Mafia,

1100
01:27:54,436 --> 01:27:58,270
which has all conveniently,
seemingly, been dealt with,

1101
01:27:58,356 --> 01:28:01,599
but everyone knows the truth.

1102
01:28:47,906 --> 01:28:50,568
I feel Al Pacino was very

1103
01:28:51,952 --> 01:28:54,159
brave in working with me

1104
01:28:54,246 --> 01:28:58,615
to take Michael outside
of the pre-fabricated,

1105
01:28:58,708 --> 01:29:02,326
Michael Corleone-type role.
I mean, starting from day one,

1106
01:29:02,420 --> 01:29:04,627
when we cut his hair,

1107
01:29:04,714 --> 01:29:08,833
which sort of really determined
the course we were going to go.

1108
01:29:08,927 --> 01:29:10,509
He wasn't going to be

1109
01:29:10,595 --> 01:29:12,513
the Michael Corleone
of the other two pictures

1110
01:29:12,597 --> 01:29:17,012
who was going to be one step
ahead of all the adversaries.

1111
01:29:17,102 --> 01:29:22,688
That he was going to be a
combination more of Marlon's character

1112
01:29:22,774 --> 01:29:26,813
in the first <i>Godfather,</i> and a kind of man

1113
01:29:26,903 --> 01:29:30,191
more concerned with
his hope of redemption,

1114
01:29:30,282 --> 01:29:33,365
and hope to be reunited with his family

1115
01:29:33,451 --> 01:29:35,988
to a hope of earning back,

1116
01:29:36,079 --> 01:29:39,367
if not the respect, but
the regard of his wife.

1117
01:29:39,457 --> 01:29:42,916
These were his concerns rather than

1118
01:29:43,003 --> 01:29:47,668
who was going to control the
cocaine business in West Long Beach

1119
01:29:47,799 --> 01:29:54,717
or these idiotic concerns that
the powerful men of our time are…

1120
01:29:54,890 --> 01:29:57,052
Who's going to own
cable or who's going to

1121
01:29:57,142 --> 01:30:00,225
figure out how they
can sell air to people.

1122
01:30:00,312 --> 01:30:05,057
Michael's concern is, I think, deeper.

1123
01:30:05,150 --> 01:30:07,767
And nothing is higher,
I would think for him,

1124
01:30:07,861 --> 01:30:09,570
than his relationship with his son,

1125
01:30:09,654 --> 01:30:13,318
who, while he wants to be
independent of his father,

1126
01:30:13,408 --> 01:30:17,618
still wants to express
something to his father,

1127
01:30:17,704 --> 01:30:21,493
"Accept me and how
I'm different, but also,

1128
01:30:21,583 --> 01:30:25,793
"understand that it means really more"

1129
01:30:25,879 --> 01:30:29,588
"that I can go my own
way and yet be your son,"

1130
01:30:29,674 --> 01:30:31,801
and love you, and
respect you as a father."

1131
01:30:31,885 --> 01:30:35,048
And I was moved by the thought

1132
01:30:35,138 --> 01:30:40,759
that this boy would sing an
old Sicilian song to his father

1133
01:30:41,102 --> 01:30:45,938
and not even know that it
was bringing back memories

1134
01:30:47,442 --> 01:30:50,935
of Michael Corleone's young wife,

1135
01:30:51,029 --> 01:30:53,896
who had been sacrificed in

1136
01:30:53,990 --> 01:30:59,235
the insane warfare between thugs.

